00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:01,375
THE FEWER CHILDREN YOU HAVE,
THE BETTER THEY ARE

2
00:01:01,458 --> 00:01:02,333
CONTRIBUTE TO YOUR COUNTRY

3
00:01:14,875 --> 00:01:18,625
SHU NA

4
00:01:55,666 --> 00:01:57,583
SUCH NICE WEATHER TODAY, GREAT FOR MOVIES.

5
00:01:57,666 --> 00:02:00,208
{\an8}AS A VIEWER, THE MORE YOU WATCH,
THE MORE YOU COMPREHEND.

6
00:02:00,708 --> 00:02:03,500
{\an8}THANK YOU TO THE DIRECTOR
AND ALL THE STAFF!

7
00:02:03,583 --> 00:02:05,625
{\an8}WE HAVE TO ACCEPT IMPERFECTION,
AS PERFECTION NO LONGER EXISTS.

8
00:02:33,666 --> 00:02:35,416
Where did you go?

9
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:36,541
I got lost.

10
00:02:36,625 --> 00:02:38,375
Are you sure this is the place?

11
00:02:39,541 --> 00:02:42,208
I'm very sure it's here.

12
00:02:44,541 --> 00:02:46,000
Why are the lights off?

13
00:02:46,083 --> 00:02:48,458
It's a power cut.
Aren't you used to them yet?

14
00:02:53,416 --> 00:02:55,416
Nurse, we are here to sell.

15
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,500
Of course you are here to sell.

16
00:02:57,583 --> 00:03:00,083
- You can't be here to buy, can you?
- You don't have to be so loud.

17
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:01,625
What are you shy about?

18
00:03:01,708 --> 00:03:03,833
All these people are here
for the same reason.

19
00:03:03,916 --> 00:03:05,125
Fill out this form.

20
00:03:05,208 --> 00:03:06,500
Wait over there.

21
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:08,958
<i>That's right.
This is not an ordinary love story.</i>

22
00:03:09,041 --> 00:03:11,958
<i>Don't misunderstand.
I don't mean the two of us.</i>

23
00:03:12,041 --> 00:03:14,291
<i>My name is Hui. I am a blogger.</i>

24
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:15,875
<i>My online nickname is "Frog Prince."</i>

25
00:03:15,958 --> 00:03:19,916
<i>This one who looks more like a toad
is my uncle, Mark Gao.</i>

26
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,416
<i>How did we end up here?</i>

27
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:25,208
<i>We will have to start this story
28 months ago.</i>

28
00:03:25,291 --> 00:03:30,708
Stop running! Stop! Give me back my money!

29
00:03:31,625 --> 00:03:33,750
- Pay me back!
- Stop running!

30
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:37,625
Pay me back!

31
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,083
Granny!

32
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,125
Granny!

33
00:03:57,458 --> 00:03:58,583
We're in a pickle!

34
00:03:58,666 --> 00:04:00,291
Pickle's good. Come on, let's eat.

35
00:04:01,083 --> 00:04:02,333
That's not funny.

36
00:04:03,416 --> 00:04:05,291
We really need to be on the run now.

37
00:04:05,375 --> 00:04:07,500
You say that every time,
but you've never run a single time.

38
00:04:07,583 --> 00:04:09,791
Even this time, you swam.

39
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:12,000
Granny! Stop kidding!

40
00:04:12,083 --> 00:04:14,333
Now what have you done?

41
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:18,041
The number given by that
don't-know-what temple struck third prize.

42
00:04:18,125 --> 00:04:20,375
But I forgot to place my bet.

43
00:04:20,458 --> 00:04:22,750
Amazing!

44
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:24,833
You're even greater than the deity.

45
00:04:24,916 --> 00:04:27,833
How could you even forget
the number given by the deity?

46
00:04:29,666 --> 00:04:31,125
What should I do now?

47
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:37,000
Granny, I'm going to bathe.

48
00:04:37,083 --> 00:04:40,541
Tell me what to do after that.

49
00:04:40,625 --> 00:04:42,125
Help me think about it.

50
00:04:46,708 --> 00:04:48,541
<i>Although I'm called "Frog Prince,"</i>

51
00:04:48,625 --> 00:04:50,375
<i>I don't want to be "a frog in the well."</i>

52
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:53,125
<i>Of course, I will take this opportunity
to go see the world!</i>

53
00:04:53,208 --> 00:04:56,916
<i>But I didn't expect that this would be
how I'd eventually meet my destiny.</i>

54
00:04:58,208 --> 00:04:59,458
Hey!

55
00:04:59,958 --> 00:05:01,916
Get in! Or are you waiting for
the cops to come?

56
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,166
<i>Like I said, he's my uncle.</i>

57
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:07,125
<i>And he's a very troublesome uncle.</i>

58
00:05:11,125 --> 00:05:13,750
Uncle! This is cool!

59
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:15,291
How's the car?

60
00:05:15,375 --> 00:05:16,750
It's really not too bad.

61
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:18,125
It's clearly written.
Here, see for yourself.

62
00:05:19,416 --> 00:05:21,666
If any more new cars come in,
remember to call me for a test drive.

63
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:23,291
- No problem.
- Otherwise, I'll be angry.

64
00:05:23,375 --> 00:05:25,291
- No problem.
- It's a deal then.

65
00:05:26,458 --> 00:05:27,916
Let's go!

66
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,208
- Mark!
- What?

67
00:05:29,291 --> 00:05:30,833
So that supercar is not yours?

68
00:05:30,916 --> 00:05:32,666
Now, I want to get a Ferrari. Can't I?

69
00:05:57,416 --> 00:06:02,500
Sorry! I'm sorry, sir. Sorry. How are you?

70
00:06:03,625 --> 00:06:05,875
Did you think you were Alonso,
to be speeding as fast?

71
00:06:05,958 --> 00:06:08,958
Of course not. I'm shooting a film now.

72
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:10,750
- Shooting a film?
- Yeah.

73
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:13,500
- Where are the actors?
- Me. I'm the actor.

74
00:06:13,583 --> 00:06:15,708
- And the cameras?
- Cameras are there. There.

75
00:06:15,791 --> 00:06:19,291
There's one there. There's one here.
There's one more there.

76
00:06:19,375 --> 00:06:21,291
Technology has become very advanced.

77
00:06:21,375 --> 00:06:24,375
There are wireless cameras everywhere.

78
00:06:24,458 --> 00:06:29,583
Yes, our crew is the best
of the best in Asia.

79
00:06:29,666 --> 00:06:33,041
Our boss is Andy Lau from Hong Kong.

80
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:35,791
- Andy Lau?
- That's right!

81
00:06:35,875 --> 00:06:38,625
- Andy Lau, I know him.
- Our producer is from China.

82
00:06:38,708 --> 00:06:40,541
Feng Xiaogang!

83
00:06:40,625 --> 00:06:42,208
Do you know Mr. Feng?

84
00:06:42,291 --> 00:06:45,250
- Mr. Feng, I know him too.
- You know Mr. Feng but not Feng Xiaogang?

85
00:06:45,333 --> 00:06:47,250
Our director is famous.

86
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:51,500
He's the Singaporean director, Jack Neo.

87
00:06:51,583 --> 00:06:53,333
- Jack Neo?
- Yes, that's him.

88
00:06:53,416 --> 00:06:54,625
- Do you like him?
- A lot!

89
00:06:54,708 --> 00:06:56,416
- I know him well. You want his autograph?
- Yes.

90
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,500
Okay, I can do that, I'll get it for you.

91
00:06:58,583 --> 00:06:59,750
What is your movie about?

92
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:03,041
I cannot tell you. It's a secret.

93
00:07:03,125 --> 00:07:04,750
Just reveal a bit.

94
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,625
Okay fine, fine.
Since we are best friends now.

95
00:07:07,708 --> 00:07:10,666
This movie is about a race car driver.

96
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:12,000
A race car driver.

97
00:07:12,083 --> 00:07:14,458
- A race car driver?
- That's right!

98
00:07:14,541 --> 00:07:18,250
- I know.
- One day, he joined the gangsters.

99
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:22,791
- Wow, that's very dangerous.
- Yeah, but that's how the script goes.

100
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:27,833
One day, his boss tells him to
smuggle illegal substances.

101
00:07:27,916 --> 00:07:30,333
- And after that?
- Drugs and other things.

102
00:07:30,416 --> 00:07:34,250
- Unfortunately, he gets caught.
- What happens in the end?

103
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:36,583
Go watch it when the film is released.

104
00:07:36,666 --> 00:07:38,208
- Then you'll know.
- Tell me a little.

105
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:41,208
Okay, okay. Apparently, the cop
who stopped him was a good person.

106
00:07:41,291 --> 00:07:44,500
- Like me. I am also a good person.
- Yes, but you are more handsome.

107
00:07:44,583 --> 00:07:46,125
- How do you know?
- For sure.

108
00:07:46,208 --> 00:07:52,916
Then the kind cop let him go.

109
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,916
Is that okay? Can I go now?
Here, smile at the camera.

110
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,708
So I'll go now, okay?

111
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:02,583
SUMMONS

112
00:08:02,666 --> 00:08:06,875
<i>By now, you'll have understood the reason
we ended up having to go sell</i>

113
00:08:06,958 --> 00:08:09,875
<i>is definitely because of this Mark Gao</i>

114
00:08:09,958 --> 00:08:13,083
<i>who thinks he knows everything
and is filled with crazy ideas.</i>

115
00:08:13,166 --> 00:08:16,875
With Super Marky,
you will all be Super Pretty!

116
00:08:16,958 --> 00:08:20,125
<i>He looks as if he needs a makeover,
yet he dares to sell beauty products.</i>

117
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,541
<i>I smell trouble!</i>

118
00:08:21,625 --> 00:08:24,083
Free of charge! Free product
demonstration. Who would like to try?

119
00:08:28,791 --> 00:08:31,291
Ladies, how can I help you?

120
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:33,375
Mark Gao, your "Snowy Cream"
has caused my face to bleed!

121
00:08:33,458 --> 00:08:36,458
And your "Whitie Mask"
has caused blackheads all over my nose!

122
00:08:37,458 --> 00:08:38,958
We want a refund!

123
00:08:40,916 --> 00:08:42,041
Ouch!

124
00:08:42,875 --> 00:08:45,916
Not a single cent left for me.

125
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:48,416
Yeah. All we have is this useless piece.

126
00:08:51,625 --> 00:08:55,416
Where there's a will there's a way.

127
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:59,083
Sell your car and we should be
covered for a while.

128
00:09:03,541 --> 00:09:06,375
I only missed one payment
and you tow my car?

129
00:09:06,458 --> 00:09:08,666
Egg roll, lotus cake, yam cake, egg tart!

130
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:09,833
- Hey!
- What?

131
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,916
Can you not mention food
at a time like this?

132
00:09:15,125 --> 00:09:17,083
- What should we do?
- What do you mean what should we do?

133
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:18,875
Earn money to buy food.

134
00:09:21,125 --> 00:09:23,041
<i>Back to my old trade.</i>

135
00:09:23,125 --> 00:09:25,750
<i>How do you survive on
one vacuum cleaner sale per month?</i>

136
00:09:25,833 --> 00:09:27,250
<i>Finally, my chance to show my prowess.</i>

137
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:28,875
<i>This is not style!</i>

138
00:09:28,958 --> 00:09:32,458
<i>Goodness, is there a job in this world
where you're paid for idling?</i>

139
00:09:32,541 --> 00:09:34,833
There is. Rob someone.

140
00:09:34,916 --> 00:09:36,125
Rob someone?

141
00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:38,333
- No way!
- Correct.

142
00:09:38,416 --> 00:09:39,583
We could be arrested by the police.

143
00:09:39,666 --> 00:09:42,125
The police don't have time to arrest you.

144
00:09:42,208 --> 00:09:43,708
If that's the case...

145
00:09:46,208 --> 00:09:48,708
- Okay then. Let's go rob someone.
- Where should we do it?

146
00:09:48,791 --> 00:09:50,250
Here.

147
00:09:51,791 --> 00:09:54,083
Are you robbing us?

148
00:09:54,166 --> 00:09:56,166
We don't have money.

149
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:59,375
- Ouch!
- Don't try us!

150
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:01,500
I know Snake Palm.

151
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:04,291
- Dragon Fist.
- Praying Mantis.

152
00:10:05,125 --> 00:10:07,291
And also Tiger Strike!

153
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:15,000
<i>To pay off our debts and buy food,
we had to resort to selling.</i>

154
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,708
Does it hurt?

155
00:10:24,708 --> 00:10:26,375
Here are your chocolates and biscuits.

156
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:32,625
- Miss.
- Yes?

157
00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:34,291
- Is this all?
- It's done.

158
00:10:34,375 --> 00:10:36,125
You must be kidding.

159
00:10:36,208 --> 00:10:38,583
Let me give you another pack of biscuits.

160
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:43,875
Stop kidding.

161
00:10:43,958 --> 00:10:45,125
We get paid, right?

162
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:49,041
No payment will be made.
Thank you for your charity.

163
00:10:49,916 --> 00:10:51,291
Charity?

164
00:10:51,375 --> 00:10:52,416
This is absurd!

165
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:55,000
We give you charity,
but who's going to give us charity?

166
00:10:55,083 --> 00:10:57,375
I donated so much blood,

167
00:10:57,458 --> 00:10:59,708
even squeezing out a few large drops.

168
00:10:59,791 --> 00:11:01,541
- We really don't get paid?
- Yeah?

169
00:11:01,625 --> 00:11:02,833
Are you sure we don't get paid?

170
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:04,500
Are you really sure we don't get paid?

171
00:11:05,583 --> 00:11:07,291
Fine! I'll take back my blood!

172
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:09,541
Sir, you can't do that!

173
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:13,916
You!

174
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,666
- Thank you for your charity.
- Sir!

175
00:11:19,291 --> 00:11:21,583
Now what else can we do?

176
00:11:22,083 --> 00:11:26,041
See if there's anything else we can sell!

177
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:39,291
BE HANDSOME, SELL HANDSOME,
BE PAID HANDSOMELY.

178
00:11:41,666 --> 00:11:43,750
Nurse, we are here to sell...

179
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:45,875
Of course you are here to sell!

180
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:48,333
- You can't be here to buy, can you?
- You don't have to be so loud.

181
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:49,833
Fill out this form.

182
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:51,083
Wait over there.

183
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:38,458
Whoa!

184
00:12:39,041 --> 00:12:40,083
What?

185
00:12:40,166 --> 00:12:41,916
- I can't do it!
- You can't do it?

186
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,750
No, the DVD player in my room
is not working.

187
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:45,291
Mine isn't working either.

188
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:48,375
- Your isn't working either?
- Not here, over there!

189
00:12:48,458 --> 00:12:50,416
- What now?
- Read the magazine!

190
00:12:51,083 --> 00:12:53,583
- I can't turn the page.
- Give it to me!

191
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,041
Didn't make it?

192
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,375
The mood just isn't right for us.

193
00:13:08,458 --> 00:13:10,458
Nurse, this needs patience.

194
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:11,541
What?

195
00:13:30,041 --> 00:13:34,000
<i>We're not perverts who go crazy
at the sight of a woman.</i>

196
00:13:34,083 --> 00:13:38,041
<i>Actually, she's my dream girl,
my princess.</i>

197
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:41,000
<i>We have a destiny!</i>

198
00:13:41,541 --> 00:13:42,916
<i>What kind of destiny?</i>

199
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,208
<i>I have to thank Mark Gao for that.</i>

200
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:46,625
<i>If not for him,</i>

201
00:13:46,708 --> 00:13:49,375
<i>my princess and I wouldn't have met.</i>

202
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:54,958
Hello?

203
00:14:00,083 --> 00:14:01,291
Can you let me drive the car?

204
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:02,916
- No.
- Why not?

205
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,250
No means no.

206
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:06,291
If you make any more noise,
I'll throw you out of the car.

207
00:14:06,375 --> 00:14:08,000
Stingy.

208
00:14:10,541 --> 00:14:12,833
- Why is it so jammed?
- There are lots of cars.

209
00:14:12,916 --> 00:14:15,958
You think I can't see that myself?
I meant, why are there so many cars?

210
00:14:24,958 --> 00:14:27,125
Drive! Quick!

211
00:14:27,208 --> 00:14:29,541
- Miss, how can I help you?
- Drive! Don't talk!

212
00:14:29,625 --> 00:14:31,625
- I'd like to, but it's jammed up ahead.
- Have you stared enough?!

213
00:14:31,708 --> 00:14:33,375
Isn't there a space over there? Quick!

214
00:14:33,458 --> 00:14:34,666
- Okay, okay.
- Quick!

215
00:14:39,458 --> 00:14:41,791
What are you staring at?! Quick! Drive!

216
00:14:42,375 --> 00:14:43,833
Quick!

217
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:48,000
Quick! Drive!

218
00:14:53,625 --> 00:14:57,833
Miss, this guy is jinxed.

219
00:14:57,916 --> 00:15:00,083
If I were you,

220
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:02,958
I'd use five types of ingredients
to wash off the bad luck.

221
00:15:03,041 --> 00:15:08,375
Use coriander, lemon grass,
grasshopper, butterfly, and bees.

222
00:15:08,458 --> 00:15:11,791
Blend them together and then...

223
00:15:12,291 --> 00:15:13,416
Hey, miss!

224
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:16,541
We met her at the same time,
and you claim to be the lucky one?

225
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,666
Who told you to say "no" earlier?

226
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:22,625
Otherwise, you would have
been the lucky one.

227
00:15:22,708 --> 00:15:25,291
{\an8}LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT WITH MY PRINCESS

228
00:15:28,416 --> 00:15:29,666
Where did you go?

229
00:15:30,708 --> 00:15:31,875
Hang on.

230
00:15:31,958 --> 00:15:34,166
I think I saw something
that shouldn't be her,

231
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:36,625
but I wouldn't mind seeing it every day.

232
00:15:36,708 --> 00:15:38,541
Look!

233
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:40,958
It's her again!

234
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,791
Miss, remember me?

235
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:51,333
Who would remember a common face
like yours?

236
00:15:51,416 --> 00:15:53,750
Miss, remember me?

237
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:55,166
The one who drove you this morning?

238
00:16:01,916 --> 00:16:04,250
Xiao Hui! It's me!

239
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:18,083
She's smiling at me.

240
00:16:18,166 --> 00:16:20,291
Are you sure you are the one
she's looking at?

241
00:16:20,375 --> 00:16:23,666
LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT WITH MY PRINCESS

242
00:16:27,375 --> 00:16:29,000
<i>Meeting once can be an accident.</i>

243
00:16:29,083 --> 00:16:30,875
<i>Twice can be a coincidence.</i>

244
00:16:30,958 --> 00:16:32,875
<i>But three times in a day?</i>

245
00:16:33,458 --> 00:16:35,250
