00:47:46,500 --> 00:47:48,500
All my things are damaged already.

750
00:47:48,583 --> 00:47:50,916
- Yeah.
- What has it got to do with me?

751
00:47:51,000 --> 00:47:52,416
What has it got to do with you?

752
00:47:53,083 --> 00:47:55,708
From now on, even if you get beaten,
owe people money,

753
00:47:55,791 --> 00:47:57,750
or become a beggar,
I'm not going to help you.

754
00:48:00,208 --> 00:48:02,083
Are you guys leaving without paying
for the damage you did?

755
00:48:02,166 --> 00:48:03,583
Is that how I taught you guys?

756
00:48:03,666 --> 00:48:05,500
Okay, we understand.

757
00:48:06,041 --> 00:48:08,000
- Come, two hundred dollars for you.
- What?

758
00:48:08,083 --> 00:48:10,291
I mean, two thousand.

759
00:48:13,541 --> 00:48:17,708
<i>Looks like Orange will be
disappearing for a while.</i>

760
00:48:17,791 --> 00:48:21,875
<i>But then, someone even
more troublesome came to us.</i>

761
00:48:23,500 --> 00:48:25,083
Mother, what brought you here?

762
00:48:25,166 --> 00:48:28,125
Didn't I WhatsApp you earlier?

763
00:48:28,208 --> 00:48:29,666
- I didn't receive anything.
- No.

764
00:48:29,750 --> 00:48:31,208
- I did.
- Nope.

765
00:48:31,291 --> 00:48:32,666
- No?
- Who's at the door?

766
00:48:34,291 --> 00:48:35,166
Who is she?

767
00:48:38,083 --> 00:48:40,125
Mark, you are the oldest. You tell me.

768
00:48:40,875 --> 00:48:42,000
She is my friend.

769
00:48:47,041 --> 00:48:50,250
- Correct!
- Friend?

770
00:48:50,333 --> 00:48:51,791
Why didn't you tell me that
you were married?

771
00:48:51,875 --> 00:48:54,416
No, she's not Uncle's wife.

772
00:48:54,500 --> 00:48:56,041
Not his wife? Then she is your wife?

773
00:48:56,125 --> 00:48:59,666
No, that's even more unlikely.

774
00:49:00,541 --> 00:49:02,875
Sorry, I need to go and lock up my car.

775
00:49:02,958 --> 00:49:05,125
- I need to go and watch him lock the car.
- You...

776
00:49:06,791 --> 00:49:09,000
Are you coming in?
If not, I'm closing the door.

777
00:49:13,875 --> 00:49:17,875
{\an8}SHU NA: "I'M NOT LETTING ANYONE
DESTROY MY HAPPINESS!"

778
00:49:18,791 --> 00:49:20,875
We just ran out like this.

779
00:49:20,958 --> 00:49:22,416
Are Shu Na and Grandma going to be okay?

780
00:49:22,500 --> 00:49:26,208
Don't think like that. Mother has
experienced a lot of things.

781
00:49:26,291 --> 00:49:28,250
Shu Na can pretty much
handle anything too.

782
00:49:28,333 --> 00:49:31,500
They are probably
having tea together by now.

783
00:49:36,541 --> 00:49:40,833
Who is the father of the baby?
Mark or Hui?

784
00:49:42,500 --> 00:49:44,125
It's none of your business.

785
00:49:44,750 --> 00:49:47,208
If we can't say she is our girlfriend,

786
00:49:47,291 --> 00:49:49,416
shall we say she is
our primary school classmate?

787
00:49:49,500 --> 00:49:51,166
You might as well say
she is a single mother

788
00:49:51,250 --> 00:49:53,041
and ditched by the father.
That's too mean!

789
00:49:53,125 --> 00:49:56,125
Don't tell me you were ditched
by some heartless man.

790
00:49:56,208 --> 00:49:58,125
I won't believe that.

791
00:49:58,208 --> 00:50:02,208
And, who is the father of that child?

792
00:50:02,916 --> 00:50:05,666
To be honest,

793
00:50:05,750 --> 00:50:06,791
I don't know either.

794
00:50:07,500 --> 00:50:11,333
Let's just be honest with Grandma
and say that we sold our sperm.

795
00:50:11,416 --> 00:50:12,791
Mother is very conservative.

796
00:50:12,875 --> 00:50:14,250
She will get a heart attack from this.

797
00:50:14,333 --> 00:50:18,541
I thought you had a good new idea
since you raised your voice,

798
00:50:18,625 --> 00:50:20,500
but it turned out to be useless.

799
00:50:20,583 --> 00:50:21,875
Why don't you think of something?

800
00:50:21,958 --> 00:50:25,166
Although this squid is only so-so quality,

801
00:50:25,250 --> 00:50:29,416
it doesn't seem like he'll lose his mind
when he is drunk.

802
00:50:31,708 --> 00:50:34,208
This is even fresher and greener.

803
00:50:35,083 --> 00:50:37,083
Such a pity

804
00:50:37,166 --> 00:50:39,208
that it has been ruined this way.

805
00:50:39,833 --> 00:50:42,375
If you don't like me,
you can go back to your own place.

806
00:50:42,458 --> 00:50:43,791
Why are you still here?

807
00:50:45,791 --> 00:50:49,000
I'm deaf. I can't hear you properly.

808
00:50:57,208 --> 00:50:59,291
So, any ideas?
How are we going to explain it to Mother?

809
00:50:59,375 --> 00:51:00,833
You think of something.

810
00:51:11,000 --> 00:51:12,000
She left.

811
00:51:13,125 --> 00:51:15,083
- Shu Na.
- Shu Na.

812
00:51:15,166 --> 00:51:17,375
- Chicken soup, good stuff.
- Good stuff.

813
00:51:18,041 --> 00:51:19,083
Come quickly.

814
00:51:19,625 --> 00:51:20,541
Go away.

815
00:51:20,625 --> 00:51:21,958
Use this for her. That's yours.

816
00:51:22,041 --> 00:51:23,416
It's the same.

817
00:51:24,625 --> 00:51:26,125
Sit down.

818
00:51:27,625 --> 00:51:29,333
Drink while it's hot. It's nice.

819
00:51:29,416 --> 00:51:31,125
Grandma spent so much time on this.

820
00:51:31,208 --> 00:51:32,708
Chicken soup?

821
00:51:33,666 --> 00:51:34,916
Let's eat.

822
00:51:35,500 --> 00:51:36,625
How is it?

823
00:51:38,458 --> 00:51:40,291
It must be good.

824
00:51:44,833 --> 00:51:45,666
What's wrong?

825
00:51:47,250 --> 00:51:48,291
What's wrong?

826
00:51:50,916 --> 00:51:53,333
Grandma, what did you put
in the chicken soup?

827
00:51:53,416 --> 00:51:56,750
Mother, even if you don't like her,
you don't have to do this.

828
00:51:56,833 --> 00:51:59,833
What are you two talking about?
Who dislikes who?

829
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:23,708
I bought some pork belly
and some Chinese herbs.

830
00:52:23,791 --> 00:52:27,708
You can take a look and check
if you are okay.

831
00:52:27,791 --> 00:52:30,375
I will use them to make some soup for you.

832
00:52:30,458 --> 00:52:34,125
It will be good for the baby.

833
00:52:34,208 --> 00:52:37,541
It's better for you to check first. I
don't want to be accused of poisoning you.

834
00:52:37,625 --> 00:52:40,333
Why? Are you feeling guilty now?

835
00:52:40,416 --> 00:52:43,000
Don't you like asking me
who the father of the baby is?

836
00:52:43,083 --> 00:52:47,000
You think I am senile or something?

837
00:52:47,666 --> 00:52:51,250
When the baby is born,
we can do a DNA check.

838
00:52:51,333 --> 00:52:54,166
Then we'll know who the father is.

839
00:52:54,250 --> 00:52:57,166
I'll still love the child
no matter who the father is.

840
00:52:57,250 --> 00:53:01,416
Whether it belongs to Mark or Hui,
it's still going to be my grandchild.

841
00:53:15,458 --> 00:53:16,583
Come with me!

842
00:53:17,083 --> 00:53:18,333
Let me go!

843
00:53:18,416 --> 00:53:19,500
What are you doing?

844
00:53:19,583 --> 00:53:22,000
What do you want?

845
00:53:27,958 --> 00:53:29,208
Don't be scared.

846
00:53:30,833 --> 00:53:32,833
Let's go!

847
00:53:34,458 --> 00:53:35,583
How dare you run?!

848
00:54:06,000 --> 00:54:07,875
Luckily, we could get away like this.

849
00:54:09,166 --> 00:54:10,791
Are you okay?

850
00:54:10,875 --> 00:54:13,500
- I am okay.
- Good.

851
00:54:13,583 --> 00:54:14,875
Be careful.

852
00:54:15,458 --> 00:54:18,041
Look ahead. Walk slowly.

853
00:54:33,458 --> 00:54:34,875
What's the matter?

854
00:54:34,958 --> 00:54:37,083
I think I've got a cramp in my leg.

855
00:54:37,166 --> 00:54:38,916
Bear with me.

856
00:54:43,291 --> 00:54:44,541
Are you feeling better?

857
00:54:45,875 --> 00:54:46,833
Grandma.

858
00:54:49,250 --> 00:54:50,458
I'm sorry.

859
00:54:54,750 --> 00:54:59,291
I had been mean to you
and you still protected me earlier.

860
00:55:03,958 --> 00:55:06,458
I think you are a decent girl.

861
00:55:07,625 --> 00:55:10,458
Look at you.
I'm sure you have suffered a lot.

862
00:55:12,500 --> 00:55:15,916
Why are those people after you?

863
00:55:18,583 --> 00:55:22,291
I had a hard life as a child.

864
00:55:23,500 --> 00:55:27,250
I used to look at those rich people,
showing off

865
00:55:27,333 --> 00:55:29,416
and always getting what they wanted.

866
00:55:29,500 --> 00:55:35,333
I promised myself that I would marry
a rich man when I grew up.

867
00:55:35,416 --> 00:55:40,208
Why did a nice girl like you
put yourself through that?

868
00:55:40,291 --> 00:55:44,083
Grandma, I didn't mean
to trouble Mark or Hui.

869
00:55:45,041 --> 00:55:48,791
It's all because that woman
tries everything to hurt me.

870
00:55:48,875 --> 00:55:50,958
She's the one who cannot give birth,

871
00:55:51,041 --> 00:55:53,208
and I am the one who carries
her husband's baby.

872
00:55:53,291 --> 00:55:55,291
She comes and attacks me.

873
00:55:55,833 --> 00:55:57,666
I really had no choice,
so I ended up here.

874
00:55:57,750 --> 00:56:00,375
Enough. I understand now.

875
00:56:09,125 --> 00:56:10,958
Grandma, wait over there.

876
00:56:14,625 --> 00:56:15,875
Hello?

877
00:56:20,833 --> 00:56:22,125
What?

878
00:56:22,833 --> 00:56:24,125
Say that again!

879
00:56:26,083 --> 00:56:27,833
How can you do that to me?!

880
00:56:27,916 --> 00:56:29,708
Do you know how much
I have given in for you?

881
00:56:33,125 --> 00:56:36,333
- What are you doing?
- I don't want this child anymore!

882
00:56:36,416 --> 00:56:39,208
Stop! You can't do this!

883
00:56:41,625 --> 00:56:44,166
Her water broke!

884
00:56:44,250 --> 00:56:47,541
Help! Hospital!

885
00:56:54,125 --> 00:56:55,625
I'm going to a father!

886
00:56:55,708 --> 00:56:57,125
It's me who's going to be a father.

887
00:56:57,833 --> 00:57:00,583
- It's me!
- It's me!

888
00:57:00,666 --> 00:57:03,333
- Come!
- Grandma! How is it?

889
00:57:03,416 --> 00:57:04,625
The baby is coming out.

890
00:57:04,708 --> 00:57:06,208
Why did Shu Na suddenly go into labor?

891
00:57:06,291 --> 00:57:09,166
Mother, don't tell me
you did something to her again.

892
00:57:09,250 --> 00:57:11,958
Scoundrel! Blaming everything on me again?

893
00:57:12,041 --> 00:57:15,625
She answered a call
and her water broke, and we're here.

894
00:57:15,708 --> 00:57:18,083
Wow! What a powerful call!

895
00:57:18,166 --> 00:57:21,041
Grandma, I heard that it's tough for
a first-time mom to go into labor.

896
00:57:21,125 --> 00:57:22,583
Does it hurt?

897
00:57:22,666 --> 00:57:28,333
Oh, my little Hui has finally grown up.

898
00:57:28,416 --> 00:57:31,000
Now, you know how to be considerate.
Good boy.

899
00:57:31,083 --> 00:57:33,500
Grandma, this is not
the right time to tease me.

900
00:57:37,083 --> 00:57:38,833
It's Orange.

901
00:57:38,916 --> 00:57:39,791
Orange?

902
00:57:42,041 --> 00:57:44,291
Cheap woman!

903
00:57:44,375 --> 00:57:48,875
You told everyone that we have broken up,
but you have been following me around.

904
00:57:48,958 --> 00:57:50,125
His ex-girlfriend.

905
00:57:50,208 --> 00:57:51,708
Who is following you?

906
00:57:51,791 --> 00:57:54,541
You, obviously! Otherwise,
why are you here at the hospital?

907
00:57:54,625 --> 00:57:56,875
Do you own this hospital?
Why can't I be here while you can?

908
00:57:56,958 --> 00:57:59,458
I came here to be a dad today.

909
00:57:59,541 --> 00:58:01,708
I came here to be a mother today.

910
00:58:01,791 --> 00:58:03,166
To be a mother?

911
00:58:03,833 --> 00:58:05,000
Are you pregnant?

912
00:58:07,916 --> 00:58:09,375
Why?

913
00:58:09,458 --> 00:58:11,541
- Why can't I be pregnant?
- Of course you can have a baby.

914
00:58:11,625 --> 00:58:15,083
As many as you want. You can have a
dolphin, a shark, anything you wish.

915
00:58:15,916 --> 00:58:17,833
Ouch! It hurts!

916
00:58:20,708 --> 00:58:23,875
- Don't think I am unwanted.
- Of course not.

917
00:58:23,958 --> 00:58:27,083
They will travel by yacht, taxi, and bus,
just to come and have you.

918
00:58:27,166 --> 00:58:29,458
They will even line up for you. Ouch!

919
00:58:30,291 --> 00:58:33,000
It hurts! Can you let go now?

920
00:58:41,250 --> 00:58:43,000
Orange said she's pregnant.

921
00:58:43,083 --> 00:58:44,666
Your girlfriend is good for you!

922
00:58:44,750 --> 00:58:46,416
- She's so cool!
- Yes, a good match for you.

923
00:58:46,500 --> 00:58:47,791
What? You both like her?

924
00:58:47,875 --> 00:58:49,708
- Then you should marry her.
- No way!

925
00:58:49,791 --> 00:58:51,916
Either his arms
or his legs would be broken.

926
00:58:52,000 --> 00:58:54,625
- He still has his head.
- No! That one is for me!

927
00:58:56,875 --> 00:58:58,083
Doctor.

928
00:58:58,166 --> 00:59:00,416
Is it a fried cake of fried sticks
(Is it a girl or a boy)?

929
00:59:00,500 --> 00:59:02,708
Is it in one piece or one stick?

930
00:59:06,416 --> 00:59:07,750
Abalone (Girl).

931
00:59:08,958 --> 00:59:13,083
Great! It's worth some money!

932
00:59:13,166 --> 00:59:15,875
It's lucky that it's not clams.

933
00:59:22,125 --> 00:59:25,458
OUR CUTE LITTLE HONEY!

934
00:59:27,208 --> 00:59:29,250
Look at Honey.

935
00:59:29,333 --> 00:59:31,833
I'm sure she is going to be a supermodel
when she grows up.

936
00:59:31,916 --> 00:59:34,250
Look at her long arms and legs,
she looks like me! Right?

937
00:59:34,333 --> 00:59:37,000
If she looks like you,
then she'd look like a drag queen.

938
00:59:37,083 --> 00:59:38,500
She looks like me more, right? Honey?

939
00:59:38,583 --> 00:59:40,750
Don't speak nonsense in front of the baby.

940
00:59:40,833 --> 00:59:42,250
Looks like you? Her skin will be so dry.

941
00:59:42,333 --> 00:59:44,166
Look! Even she is objecting!

942
00:59:44,250 --> 00:59:45,916
Flat chest!

943
00:59:46,875 --> 00:59:50,375
Honey doesn't look like either of us.
She looks like her mother, right?

944
01:00:10,500 --> 01:00:12,125
- Hello?
<i>- Bitch!</i>

945
01:00:12,208 --> 01:00:15,166
<i>I checked and found out that
you had miscarried our baby</i>

946
01:00:15,250 --> 01:00:17,583
<i>and then went for artificial insemination.</i>

947
01:00:17,666 --> 01:00:19,083
<i>Are you trying to make a fool of me?</i>

948
01:00:19,166 --> 01:00:21,833
<i>Let me tell you, you won't get
a single cent from me!</i>

949
01:00:21,916 --> 01:00:24,125
What? Say that again!

950
01:00:24,208 --> 01:00:25,833
How can you do that to me?

951
01:00:25,916 --> 01:00:27,750
Do you know how much
I have given in for you?

952
01:00:48,291 --> 01:00:49,833
Guys, your voices are so unbearable.

953
01:00:49,916 --> 01:00:51,500
- It's you!
- You made her cry.

954
01:00:51,583 --> 01:00:54,250
Honey, let Grandma feed you, okay?

955
01:00:55,916 --> 01:00:59,583
Honey, how can you be so cute?

956
01:01:00,916 --> 01:01:02,208
Honey, smile!

957
01:01:18,000 --> 01:01:19,833
To change diapers, open up the legs.

958
01:01:19,916 --> 01:01:26,666
You wrap this up,
slip it under this side, wrap tightly,

959
01:01:26,750 --> 01:01:29,291
and secure it when the safety pin.

960
01:01:31,166 --> 01:01:32,375
- Are you nuts?
- Mother,

961
01:01:32,458 --> 01:01:34,166
I'm worried that you might hurt her.
It looks painful!

962
01:01:34,250 --> 01:01:35,750
If you are so good, you do it!

963
01:01:40,625 --> 01:01:43,750
You can't see me.

964
01:01:43,833 --> 01:01:47,375
Open the legs, and then fold this up.

965
01:01:47,458 --> 01:01:50,583
Pull this from the right,
and then from the left.

966
01:01:50,666 --> 01:01:51,916
Done!

967
01:01:54,500 --> 01:01:56,625
How smart! Everything comes out!

968
01:01:56,708 --> 01:01:58,000
Smelly!

969
01:01:58,708 --> 01:02:01,041
Honey looks like me, she's so cute!

970
01:02:03,458 --> 01:02:06,125
Enough. Stop playing with her,
come and eat.

971
01:02:06,208 --> 01:02:09,875
Honey, let's go and eat.

972
01:02:09,958 --> 01:02:12,333
What a luxury meal!

973
01:02:12,416 --> 01:02:15,125
Of course! It's Honey's baby shower today.

974
01:02:15,208 --> 01:02:17,250
A good day for me, as a grandma.

975
01:02:17,333 --> 01:02:19,208
She's so cute!

976
01:02:19,291 --> 01:02:20,833
Our little Honey is the prettiest baby.

977
01:02:20,916 --> 01:02:23,500
Honey looks like her mother.

978
01:03:12,458 --> 01:03:14,208
Honey is a month old now.

979
01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:16,666
It's time for me to leave.

980
01:03:18,166 --> 01:03:19,708
Grandma.

981
01:03:22,583 --> 01:03:24,375
I know this is not easy for you.

982
01:03:25,250 --> 01:03:27,333
But you should do your best
to bring up your daughter.

983
01:03:29,833 --> 01:03:31,625
I believe you can do it.

984
01:03:40,041 --> 01:03:46,416
Although this is not an expensive pendant,

985
01:03:47,375 --> 01:03:49,500
it has been with me for many years.

986
01:03:50,708 --> 01:03:52,791
Let's give this to Honey.

987
01:03:52,875 --> 01:03:55,458
Hopefully, it will bless her
with good fortune.

988
01:03:55,541 --> 01:03:56,791
Grandma.

989
01:04:00,250 --> 01:04:03,291
I may not know
what really happened to you,

990
01:04:04,583 --> 01:04:09,416
but your daughter is definitely
your new future.

991
01:04:10,166 --> 01:04:11,791
A new beginning.

992
01:04:15,375 --> 01:04:17,291
You should cherish it.

993
01:04:43,375 --> 01:04:48,291
{\an8}SHU NA: WHY DO MOTHERS ALWAYS
CHOOSE TO LEAVE?

994
01:05:09,875 --> 01:05:10,916
Hello?

995
01:05:13,000 --> 01:05:14,083
Hello?

996
01:05:17,083 --> 01:05:18,375
<i>Hello?</i>

997
01:05:20,291 --> 01:05:21,791
Is that you, Xiao Na?

998
01:05:25,208 --> 01:05:26,500
Xiao Na.

999
